{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5b19f5c9-e9a8-46c4-a4b5-b687c515c0bc","content":"The project directory doesn't exist yet, but here's what you need to configure in your `.csproj` to publish as a `dotnet tool`:\n\n### Required `.csproj` properties\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n\n  <!-- Makes it installable via: dotnet tool install -g MyMcpServer -->\n  <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n  <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n  <!-- NuGet metadata -->\n  <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n  <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n  <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n  <Description>An MCP server for …</Description>\n  <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n  <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### Publishing steps\n\n```bash\n# 1. Pack\ndotnet pack -c Release\n\n# 2. Push to NuGet.org (get API key from nuget.org/account/apikeys)\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_API_KEY --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Key points\n\n- **`PackAsTool`** is the critical property — it tells `dotnet pack` to produce a tool package.\n- **`ToolCommandName`** sets the CLI command name users will invoke (defaults to the assembly name if omitted).\n- The project **must** target `Exe` (`OutputType`).\n- Users install with: `dotnet tool install -g MyMcpServer`\n- For stdio MCP transport, no additional config is needed — the tool just reads stdin/writes stdout as usual.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8788fc9a-c70e-4aa0-a23b-966358f1cf58","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The project doesn't exist yet. The user is asking what they need to configure, not asking me to create the project. Let me provide guidance on what's needed to publish a .NET tool to NuGet.org.","outputTokens":535,"requestId":"7FCA:29D6CF:71D8D62:7D81103:69F15C03"},"id":"efeb0ea3-d90d-4ff5-834c-91d6b55204a8","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:17:05.930Z","parentId":"25bfaf7c-4f49-4ee9-a459-3f6fde608cd5"}
